MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

96-1274. State ex rel. Berman v. Russo.

In Prohibition. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of prohibition. Upon consideration of relator’s expedited motion for stay of common pleas court proceedings or immediate ruling on a relator’s complaint,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
